definitions.definition: An image suitable to overlay ( superimpose ) over another (as for example a gel for an overhead projector , a slide that complements another slide as a superimposition for it, or a digital virtual equivalent of these); its coloration is adjusted to contrast with the underlying image (for example, text may be white instead of black in areas where the background is dark).

main_definition: ( photography , graphic arts ) An image suitable to overlay ( superimpose ) over another (as for example a gel for an overhead projector , a slide that complements another slide as a superimposition for it, or a digital virtual equivalent of these); its coloration is adjusted to contrast with the underlying image (for example, text may be white instead of black in areas where the background is dark).
